---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 items-center mb-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <img class="mx-auto rounded" src="/img/holly-barnard-phd-pediatric-developmental-neuropsychologist.png" alt="Dr Barnard" />
        <h1 class="mt-4">Dr. Barnard <span class="block text-sm">Ph.D., ABPP-CN</span></h1>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Pediatric & Developmental Neuropsychology</h2>
        <figure>
          <blockquote>
            <p>
              I became a neuropsychologist because, like many others out there, I had a loved one who experienced developmental delays and suffered a traumatic brain injury due to medical complications. After watching my family members struggle endlessly to find a person who could bring it all together and help us find a path forward, I decided to become that person.
            </p>
          </blockquote>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div>
        <h1>What is Neuropsychology?</h1>
        <p>A neuropsychologist is an expert in the impact of atypical development (e.g., ASD, learning disorders, spina bifida), injury (e.g., Traumatic Brain Injury, birth trauma), disease (e.g., tumor, meningitis), and decline on the brain.</p>

        <p>Patients can present with a number of complex conditions that, as they grow and mature, impact how they think, learn, and behave. A neuropsychologist helps patients, parents, and teachers to understand a person's brain and the way they function best, in case of:</p>

        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Attention-Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder</li>
          <li>Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD)</li>
          <li>Epilepsy</li>
          <li>Genetic/Chromosomal Disorders</li>
          <li>Hearing Loss</li>
          <li>History of Brain Tumor</li>
          <li>History of Neurologic Infections</li>
          <li>Hydrocephalus</li>
          <li>Metabolic Disorders</li>
          <li>Neurodevelopmental Disorders</li>
          <li>Oxygen Deprivation</li>
          <li>Specific Learning Disorders</li>
          <li>Structural Abnormalities of the Brain</li>
          <li>Toxic Encephalopathy</li>
          <li>Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)</li>
          <li>Vascular Events/Conditions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <img class="mx-auto" src="/img/we-all-have-our-different-needs.png" alt="Different needs" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="text-center">
      <img class="mx-auto" src="/img/dot-divider.svg" width="150" alt="divider" />
      <h1 class="mt-6">Ready to explore your full potential?</h1>
      <p class="max-w-md mx-auto mt-4">Contact Dr. Barnard for a free phone or e-mail consultation to determine whether the practice is a good fit for your child.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
